<item>
            <title>[LU-3567] kernel update [SLES11 SP3]</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3567</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;looking at &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.suse.com/products/server/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://www.suse.com/products/server/&lt;/a&gt; it&apos;s apparent that SuSE has now publicly announced SLES11 SP3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Need to carefully schedule the cutover from one version to another.  Maybe we need to stage using SP3 instead of SP2 somewhere before using it everywhere?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Need to make decisions about sticking to the policy of supporting only one version of any distro.  It&apos;s possible to have base and ldiskfs patches for both SP2 and SP3, but it would be easier to drop support for SP2 and support only SP3.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="19710">LU-3567</key>
            <summary>kernel update [SLES11 SP3]</summary>
