                                    <watches>7</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="67826" author="spitzcor" created="Fri, 27 Sep 2013 16:23:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bob, yup! Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="67164" author="pjones" created="Fri, 20 Sep 2013 20:44:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.5.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="66417" author="bogl" created="Wed, 11 Sep 2013 21:11:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Just in case it&apos;s not obvious from looking at the submitted patches, we chose to continue supporting building for SP2 as well as building for SP3.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65984" author="bogl" created="Fri, 6 Sep 2013 21:44:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7580&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7580&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62551" author="spitzcor" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2013 15:55:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That would be acceptable if SLES 11 SP2 won&apos;t be supported at all with 2.5.  However, I would suggest that 2.5 would support both SP2 &amp;amp; SP3.  But it is more problematic since b2_5 might have long legs due to being dubbed the next maintenance branch.  Maybe it would be acceptable to drop SP2 support in a later 2.5 release after everyone has been given an appropriate amount of time to upgrade to SP3?  Did we already take up client OS support with the CDWG?  Even if so, perhaps we should take another look at it.  It should be possible to support both side by side.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="62547" author="simmonsja" created="Thu, 18 Jul 2013 15:44:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Since no Lustre maintenance branches support SLES11SP2 which requires a new installation anyways it would be IMO best to move to SLES11 SP3. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
